  "body": "Hi,\r\n\r\nI forgot to update my Erigon instance before the London HF. I did it yesterday, but the it seems to be stuck now. \r\n\r\nIt hasn't progressed from block number 13107517, and and the logs always look like this:\r\n\r\n```\r\nSep 08 13:09:10 puc erigon[57953]: [INFO] [09-08|13:09:10.928] Regenerated local transaction journal    transactions=0 accounts=0\r\nSep 08 13:09:14 puc erigon[57953]: [INFO] [09-08|13:09:14.062] [1/18 Headers] Wrote block headers       number=13107517 blk/second=0.000 alloc=\"662.51 MiB\" sys=\"5.20 GiB\"\r\nSep 08 13:09:44 puc erigon[57953]: [INFO] [09-08|13:09:44.061] [1/18 Headers] Wrote block headers       number=13107517 blk/second=0.000 alloc=\"749.37 MiB\" sys=\"5.20 GiB\"\r\nSep 08 13:09:44 puc erigon[57953]: [INFO] [09-08|13:09:44.062] [1/18 Headers] Processed                 highest inserted=0 age=52y5mo1w\r\nSep 08 13:09:44 puc erigon[57953]: [INFO] [09-08|13:09:44.062] [1/18 Headers] DONE                      in=2m30.001269265s\r\nSep 08 13:09:44 puc erigon[57953]: [INFO] [09-08|13:09:44.064] Update current block for the RPC API     from=13107518 to=13107517\r\nSep 08 13:09:44 puc erigon[57953]: [INFO] [09-08|13:09:44.064] [1/18 Headers] Waiting for headers...    from=13107517\r\nSep 08 13:09:54 puc erigon[57953]: [INFO] [09-08|13:09:54.154] [p2p] GoodPeers                          eth66=30 eth65=26\r\nSep 08 13:10:14 puc erigon[57953]: [INFO] [09-08|13:10:14.066] [1/18 Headers] Wrote block headers       number=13107517 blk/second=0.000 alloc=\"823.32 MiB\" sys=\"5.20 GiB\"\r\n```\r\n\r\nIs there a way to recover it? Or do I have to resync?\r\n\r\nThanks",
